<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Lolium</i> <i>perenne</i> is dominant or co-dominant with other non-natives in the herbaceous layer such as <i>Agrostis</i> <i>stolonifera</i>, <i>Avena</i> <i>fatua</i>, <i>Brassica</i> <i>nigra</i>, <i>Bromus</i> <i>diandrus</i>, <i>Bromus</i> <i>hordeaceus</i>, <i>Cirsium</i> <i>vulgare</i>, <i>Festuca</i> <i>arundinacea</i>, <i>Holcus</i> <i>lanatus</i>, <i>Hordeum</i> <i>marinum</i>, <i>Leontodon</i> <i>saxatilis</i>, <i>Lotus</i> <i>corniculatus</i>, <i>Phalaris</i> <i>aquatica</i>, <i>Poa</i> <i>pratensis</i>, <i>Rumex</i> <i>crispus</i> and <i>Trifolium</i> spp. Native species which may be present at much lower cover include <i>Alopecurus</i> <i>aequalis</i>, <i>Asclepias</i> <i>fascicularis</i>, <i>Centaurium</i> <i>muehlenbergii</i>, <i>Cryptantha</i> <i>flaccida</i>, <i>Euphorbia</i> <i>spathulata</i>, <i>Hordeum</i> <i>brachyantherum</i>, <i>Leymus</i> <i>triticoides</i>, <i>Microseris</i> <i>douglasii</i>, <i>Nassella</i> <i>pulchra</i>, <i>Nasturtium</i> <i>officinale</i> and <i>Plantago</i> <i>erecta</i>. Emergent trees and shrubs may be present at low cover. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 1 m; cover is intermittent to continuous. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Lolium perenne</i> ≥ 50% relative cover, native plants < 15% relative cover, and <i>Bromus hordeaceus, Hordeum</i> spp. may be present in lower cover (Keeler-Wolf and Vaghti 2000).</li>
		
		<li><i>Lolium perenne</i> > 50% relative cover, with conspicuous <i>Lotus corniculatus</i> (Boul et al. 2021b).</li>
		
		<li><i>Lolium perenne</i> > 50% relative cover, or > 30% relative cover with <i>Avena</i> spp., <i>Bromus</i> spp., <i>Hordeum marinum, H. murinum, Medicago, Trifolium subterraneum, Elymus caput-medusae</i>, and other non-natives in the herbaceous layer. Native species are typically less than 10% relative cover (Buck-Diaz et al. 2021, Sikes et al. 2021).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Lowlands with periodic flooding, disked fields, and uplands including serpentine substrates. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (2012 national list) recognizes <i>Lolium perenne</i> as a FAC plant. </div>
</div>

        
